intervene /ˌɪntəˈviːn/

(intervening,intervened,intervenes) 

1. V-I If you intervene in a situation, you become involved in it and try to change it. 干预 

例： The situation calmed down when police intervened. 警察干预后，局势平静了下来。 

2. V-I If you intervene , you interrupt a conversation in order to add something to it. 插话 

例： Hernandez intervened and told me to stop it. 贺尔南德兹插话，不让我再说下去。 

3. V-I If an event intervenes , it happens suddenly in a way that stops, delays, or prevents something from happening. 干扰 

例： The mailboat arrived on Friday mornings unless bad weather intervened. 除非受到恶劣天气的干扰，邮船于星期五上午到达。

